FBIS4-67127 "jptdd020__l94112" JPRS-TDD-94-020-L JPRS Narcotics 24 April 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY Brazilian Attempting To Smuggle 5 Kg of Cocaine Arrested Brazilian Attempting To Smuggle 5 Kg of Cocaine Arrested NC0205084194 Istanbul SABAH in Turkish 24 Apr 94 p 3 NC0205084194 Istanbul SABAH Turkish BFN [Text] Damaris Lisoba Gomes Sardinia, 28, was detained at Ataturk Airport in Istanbul for trying to smuggle 5 kg of cocaine into Turkey yesterday. Sardinia, who is a citizen of Brazil, arrived in Turkey from Spain. The police discovered 5 kg of cocaine in the pockets of her slacks in her suitcase after she passed through immigration control. She was handed over to the officials of the Narcotics Department after the police at the airport interrogated her.
